Looking at the proof goal, I need to show that `(fun g => comp g (Category.id Y)) = Category.id (Hom c Y)`.

The left side is a function that takes `g : Hom c Y` and returns `g ≫ id Y`.
The right side is `Category.id (Hom c Y)`, which by definition is the identity function on `Hom c Y`.

By the right identity law of categories, `g ≫ id Y = g`, so these functions are equal.

```lean
def Hom_c_? {α : Type*} [Category α] (c : α) : Functor α Type where
  F Y := Hom c Y
  homF {Y Z : α} (f : Hom Y Z) (g : Hom c Y) := g ≫ f
  map_id Y := by
    funext g
    simp [Category.id, comp_id]
```
